text: Caleb Powell (1793 – 24 February 1881) was an Irish Repeal Association and Whig politician. Powell was first elected Whig MP for at the 1841 general election and held the seat until 1847 when, standing as a Repeal Association candidate, he was defeated. ==References== ==External links== * Category:UK MPs 1841–1847 Category:Whig (British political party) MPs for Irish constituencies Category:1793 births Category:1881 deaths
